flowRoot.flowPara: Tomokumo is an Android application designed to help college students. The application keeps track of classes and events, groups friends
into circles, locates friends and other nearby people using Tomokumo, and creates meetings with circles of friends.
Form groups of friends into circles
View locations of friends in your circles
Import your existing class schedule from Google Calendar
Create or remove classes from your schedule
Let your friends know when you are in class
Invite circles of friends to a meeting
Give your meeting a name, description, address, and date
Displays the location of your meeting on Google Maps

The application allows users to set up a Tomokumo account. Their user information then gets stored on the server so the application can retrieve it the next time that user logs in. The application also retrieves and stores additional information on the server in order to keep track of the user's circles, meetings, and settings.

The server hosts a web server and an SQL database. The web server takes in requests based on the links that are accessed. Then, the web server queries the database, returning or storing the given information based on which page was accessed.
